ygData.subject: Re: Dwarven Paladin Guild
ygData.msgSnippet: Tunare embraces all her children, from the pure High elves to the half-blessed.  Come to the Paladin Temple in Felwithe, Master Tynkale will greet you kindly
ygData.messageBody:
Tunare embraces all her children, from the pure High elves to the
half-blessed. Come to the Paladin Temple in Felwithe, Master Tynkale will
greet you kindly and help you continue your studies and training as a
warrior of the Gods.

*-----Original Message-----
*From: John Lyons [mailto:jjl1@...]
*Sent: Tuesday, April 20, 1999 2:42 PM
*To: eqpaladin@onelist.com
*Subject: [eqpaladin] Dwarven Paladin Guild
*
*
*From: John Lyons <jjl1@...>
*
*Greetings all,
*
*I was wondering whether or not the dwarf paladin guildmasters
*will train
*me. I'm a half-elf based out of Freeport, so its not too hard
*for me to
*come over to Kaladim. However, if I'm there, I would like to
*be able to
*train if I have to. I was over there when I was level 8 or so, and the
*dwarf I talked to told me he would have nothing to do with me. If
*there's another guilmaster that I missed, please let me know. If anyone
*ever wants to go out adventuring, I play on the Karana server
*and can be
*currently found in Riverval. Farewell
*
*Valandil
